.TH "drm_handle_vblank" 9 "drm_handle_vblank" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_handle_vblank \- handle a vblank event
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" drm_handle_vblank
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pipe "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "pipe" 12
index of CRTC where this event occurred
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Drivers should call this routine in their vblank interrupt handlers to
update the vblank counter and send any signals that may be pending.

This is the legacy version of \fBdrm_crtc_handle_vblank\fP.
